{"metadata":{"masechet_en":"Bava Batra","masechet_he":"בבא בתרא","daf":"97B","perek_title":"המוכר פירות","perek_number":6},"english":["<b>As Rava says: A person may squeeze</b> the juice from <b>a cluster of grapes and</b> then <b>recite the sanctification of the</b> Shabbat <b>day over it.</b>","<b>Rather,</b> Rav’s statement is <b>to exclude</b> wine that is taken <b>from</b> the <b>mouth of</b> the barrel, which has scum floating in it, <b>and</b> wine taken <b>from</b> the <b>bottom of</b> the barrel, which contains the pomace. The Gemara challenges this: <b>But didn’t Rabbi Ḥiyya teach: One may not bring</b> wine that is taken <b>from</b> the <b>mouth of</b> the barrel <b>or from</b> the <b>bottom of</b> the barrel as a libation <i>ab initio</i>, <b>but if one brought</b> it as a libation <b>it is valid</b> after the fact? Accordingly, it should be fit for use for the sanctification of the Shabbat day.","<b>Rather,</b> Rav’s statement is <b>to exclude black wine, <i>borek</i></b> wine, <b>sweet wine [<i>heiliston</i>],</b> wine <b>from</b> the <b>cellar,</b> and wine made <b>from raisins.</b> The Gemara challenges: <b>But isn’t it taught</b> in a <i>baraita</i>: <b>With regard to all of</b> these types of wine, <b>one may not bring</b> them as a libation <i>ab initio</i>, <b>but if one brought</b> one of them as a libation <b>it is valid</b> after the fact. Accordingly, it should be fit for use for the sanctification of the Shabbat day.","<b>Rather,</b> Rav’s statement serves <b>to exclude souring wine, diluted</b> wine, wine that has been left <b>uncovered,</b> as there is a concern that a snake may have injected its venom into it, <b>and</b> wine made <b>from</b> grape <b>pomace, and</b> wine that has a <b>foul odor. As it is taught</b> in a <i>baraita</i>: <b>With regard to all of</b> these types of wine, <b>one may not bring</b> them as a libation, <b>and if one brought</b> one of them as a libation, <b>it is disqualified.</b>","The Gemara asks again: Rav’s statement serves <b>to exclude which</b> of these types of wine? <b>If</b> one suggests Rav intended <b>to exclude souring</b> wine, that cannot be, as the status of wine that tastes like wine but has the odor of vinegar <b>is the</b> subject of a <b>dispute between Rabbi Yoḥanan and Rabbi Yehoshua ben Levi</b> (96a).","<b>If</b> one suggests that Rav’s statement serves <b>to exclude diluted</b> wine, why would such wine be disqualified for the sanctification of the Shabbat day? Diluting wine <b>is an improvement of it, as Rabbi Yosei, son of Rabbi Ḥanina, says:</b> Even though the Rabbis disagree with Rabbi Eliezer and hold that over undiluted wine one recites the blessing: Who created the fruit of the vine, nevertheless the <b>Rabbis concede to Rabbi Eliezer with regard to a cup</b> used <b>for a blessing,</b> such as the cup of wine over which Grace after Meals is recited, <b>that one does not recite</b> the <b>blessing over it until he adds water to it</b> to make it palatable.","<b>If</b> one suggests that Rav’s statement serves <b>to exclude</b> wine that has been left <b>uncovered,</b> it would be unnecessary for Rav to teach this, because such wine, which <b>is dangerous</b> to drink, as a snake may have injected its venom into it, is already forbidden.","<b>If</b> one suggests that Rav’s statement serves <b>to exclude</b> wine made <b>from pomace, what are the circumstances? If</b> it is referring to a case <b>where one poured three</b> jugs of water over the pomace <b>and</b> the volume of the resulting beverage <b>came to four</b> jugs, that <b>is</b> considered <b>full-fledged wine,</b> which may certainly be used for the sanctification of the Shabbat day. <b>If</b> it is referring to <b>where one poured three</b> jugs of water over the pomace, <b>and</b> the resulting beverage <b>came to three and a half</b> jugs, this <b>is the</b> subject of a <b>dispute</b> between <b>the Rabbis and <i>Aḥerim</i>,</b> and the <i>halakha</i> is in accordance with the opinion of the Rabbis, who rule that it is not regarded as wine.","<b>Rather,</b> Rav’s statement serves <b>to exclude</b> wine <b>that</b> has <b>a foul odor. And if you wish, say</b> that <b>actually</b> his statement serves <b>to exclude</b> wine that has been left <b>uncovered, and</b> it teaches the novelty that <b>even though one passes it through a sieve, in accordance with</b> the opinion of <b>Rabbi Neḥemya</b> (see <i>Terumot</i> 8:7), <b>nevertheless,</b> it still may not be used for the sanctification of the Shabbat day. This is because it is disrespectful to use inferior wine for a mitzva, as derived from the verse in which God rebukes the Jewish people for offering lame animals as offerings: <b>“Present it now unto your governor; will he be pleased with you or will he accept your person?</b> says the Lord of hosts” (Malachi 1:8).","<b>Rav Kahana, father-in-law of Rav Mesharshiyya, asked Rava:</b> With regard to using <b>white wine</b> for libations and for the sanctification of the Shabbat day, <b>what is</b> the <i>halakha</i>? <b>He said to him</b> in response that the verse states: <b>“Do not look upon the wine when it is red,</b> when it gives its color in the cup, when it glides down smoothly” (Proverbs 23:31), which indicates that red wine is considered to be of a superior quality.","§ The mishna teaches: When purchasing <b>jugs</b> of wine <b>in the Sharon</b> region, he accepts upon himself that up to ten inferior-quality jugs may be present in each hundred jugs purchased. <b>It was taught</b> in a <i>baraita</i>: The buyer must accept ten inferior-quality jugs in one hundred only when even those ten <b>inferior-quality jugs</b> are <b>beautiful and sealed with pitch</b> to strengthen them.","<strong>MISHNA:</strong> If one <b>sells wine to another and</b> then <b>it sours,</b> the seller <b>does not bear</b> financial <b>responsibility for its</b> loss. <b>But if it is known</b> of this seller <b>that his wine</b> always <b>sours, then this</b> sale <b>is a mistaken transaction,</b> i.e., one based upon false assumptions, as the buyer intended to purchase wine that would maintain its quality; therefore, the seller must reimburse the buyer. <b>And if</b> the seller <b>said to</b> the buyer: It is <b>wine</b>"],"gemara":[{"right":"275px","width":"380px","text":"<span class=\"sentence\" id=\"0\" type=\"start\">☆</span>דְּאָמַר <span class=\"name-reference-marker name-reference-amora\" data-authority-id=\"2582\" data-full-name=\"Rava\" data-name-he=\"רָבָא\" data-sage-type=\"amora\" title=\"Rava, fourth-generation Amora\">רָבָא</span><span class=\"ein_mishpat_marker\" data-ein-mishpat-id=\"0\" data-marker-letter=\"א\">א</span>: סוֹחֵט אָדָם אֶשְׁכּוֹל שֶׁל עֲנָבִים,","segment_ids":[0]},{"right":"275px","width":"380px","text":"וְאוֹמֵר עָלָיו קִידּוּשׁ הַיּוֹם! <span class=\"sentence\" id=\"1\" type=\"start\">&star;</span>וְאֶלָּא לְמַעוֹטֵי","segment_ids":[1]},{"right":"275px","width":"380px","text":"מִפִּיהָ וּמִשּׁוּלֶיהָ? וְהָא תָּנֵי <span class=\"name-reference-marker name-reference-amora\" data-sage-type=\"amora\" title=\"Rabbi Ḥiyya bar Rabbi I, first-generation I Amora\" data-authority-id=\"1088\" data-full-name=\"Rabbi Ḥiyya bar Rabbi I\" data-name-he=\"רבי חייא רובה\">רַבִּי חִיָּיא</span>: מִפִּיהָ","segment_ids":[1]},{"right":"275px","width":"380px","text":"<span class=\"ein_mishpat_marker\" data-ein-mishpat-id=\"1\" data-marker-letter=\"ב\">ב</span>וּמִשּׁוּלֶיהָ לֹא יָבִיא, וְאִם הֵבִיא – כָּשֵׁר! <span class=\"sentence\" id=\"2\" type=\"start\">☆</span>וְאֶלָּא","segment_ids":[2]},{"right":"275px","width":"380px","text":"לְמַעוֹטֵי יַיִן כּוּשִׁי; בּוֹרֵק; הֵילִיסְטוֹן; שֶׁל מַרְתֵּף;","segment_ids":[2]},{"right":"275px","width":"380px","text":"שֶׁל צִמּוּקִים? וְהָא תַּנְיָא: בְּכוּלָּן <span class=\"ein_mishpat_marker\" data-ein-mishpat-id=\"2\" data-marker-letter=\"ג\">ג</span>לֹא יָבִיא, וְאִם הֵבִיא –","segment_ids":[2]},{"right":"275px","width":"380px","text":"כָּשֵׁר! <span class=\"sentence\" id=\"3\" type=\"start\">&star;</span>וְאֶלָּא לְמַעוֹטֵי יַיִן קוֹסֵס; מָזוּג;","segment_ids":[3]},{"right":"275px","width":"380px","text":"מְגוּלֶּה; וְשֶׁל שְׁמָרִים; וְשֶׁרֵיחוֹ רַע – דְּתַנְיָא: בְּכוּלָּן","segment_ids":[3]},{"right":"275px","width":"380px","text":"<span class=\"ein_mishpat_marker\" data-ein-mishpat-id=\"3\" data-marker-letter=\"ד\">ד</span>לֹא יָבִיא, וְאִם הֵבִיא – פָּסוּל. <span class=\"sentence\" id=\"4\" type=\"start\">☆</span>לְמַעוֹטֵי מַאי? אִי","segment_ids":[4]},{"right":"275px","width":"380px","text":"לְמַעוֹטֵי קוֹסֵס, פְּלוּגְתָּא <span class=\"name-reference-marker name-reference-amora\" data-sage-type=\"amora\" title=\"Rabbi Yoḥanan II, second-generation Amora\" data-authority-id=\"1570\" data-full-name=\"Rabbi Yoḥanan II\" data-name-he=\"רבי יוחנן\">דְּרַבִּי יוֹחָנָן</span> <span class=\"name-reference-marker name-reference-amora\" data-sage-type=\"amora\" title=\"Rabbi Yehoshua ben Levi, first-generation II Amora\" data-authority-id=\"1544\" data-full-name=\"Rabbi Yehoshua ben Levi\" data-name-he=\"רבי יהושע בן לוי\" data-crossline-group=\"name-ref-crossline-5905\">וְרַבִּי יְהוֹשֻׁעַ</span>","segment_ids":[4]},{"right":"275px","width":"380px","text":"<span class=\"name-reference-marker name-reference-amora\" data-authority-id=\"1544\" data-crossline-group=\"name-ref-crossline-5905\" data-full-name=\"Rabbi Yehoshua ben Levi\" data-name-he=\"רבי יהושע בן לוי\" data-sage-type=\"amora\" title=\"Rabbi Yehoshua ben Levi, first-generation II Amora\">בֶּן לֵוִי</span> הִיא! <span class=\"sentence\" id=\"5\" type=\"start\">☆</span>אִי לְמַעוֹטֵי מָזוּג, <span class=\"ein_mishpat_marker\" data-ein-mishpat-id=\"4\" data-marker-letter=\"ה\">ה</span>עַלּוֹיֵי עַלְּיֵיהּ –","segment_ids":[5]},{"right":"275px","width":"380px","text":"דְּאָמַר <span class=\"name-reference-marker name-reference-amora\" data-sage-type=\"amora\" title=\"Rabbi Yosei bar Ḥanina, second-generation Amora\" data-authority-id=\"1689\" data-full-name=\"Rabbi Yosei bar Ḥanina\" data-name-he=\"רבי יוסי ברבי חנינא\">רַבִּי יוֹסֵי בְּרַבִּי חֲנִינָא</span>: מוֹדִים חֲכָמִים <span class=\"name-reference-marker name-reference-tanna\" data-sage-type=\"tanna\" title=\"Rabbi Eliezer ben Hyrcanus, third-generation Tanna\" data-authority-id=\"417\" data-full-name=\"Rabbi Eliezer ben Hyrcanus\" data-name-he=\"רבי אליעזר בן הורקנוס\" data-crossline-group=\"name-ref-crossline-5907\">לְרַבִּי</span>","segment_ids":[5]},{"right":"275px","width":"380px","text":"<span class=\"name-reference-marker name-reference-tanna\" data-sage-type=\"tanna\" title=\"Rabbi Eliezer ben Hyrcanus, third-generation Tanna\" data-authority-id=\"417\" data-full-name=\"Rabbi Eliezer ben Hyrcanus\" data-name-he=\"רבי אליעזר בן הורקנוס\" data-crossline-group=\"name-ref-crossline-5907\">אֱלִיעֶזֶר</span> בְּכוֹס שֶׁל בְּרָכָה, שֶׁאֵין מְבָרְכִין עָלָיו","segment_ids":[5]},{"right":"275px","width":"380px","text":"עַד שֶׁיִּתֵּן לְתוֹכוֹ מַיִם! <span class=\"sentence\" id=\"6\" type=\"start\">☆</span>אִי <span class=\"ein_mishpat_marker\" data-ein-mishpat-id=\"5\" data-marker-letter=\"ו\">ו</span>לְמַעוֹטֵי מְגוּלֶּה,","segment_ids":[6]},{"right":"275px","width":"380px","text":"סַכָּנָה הִיא! <span class=\"sentence\" id=\"7\" type=\"start\">&star;</span>אִי לְמַעוֹטֵי שֶׁל שְׁמָרִים, הֵיכִי דָמֵי?","segment_ids":[7]},{"right":"275px","width":"380px","text":"אִי דִּרְמָא <span class=\"ein_mishpat_marker\" data-ein-mishpat-id=\"6\" data-marker-letter=\"ז\">ז</span>תְּלָתָא וַאֲתָא אַרְבְּעָה, חַמְרָא מְעַלְּיָא","segment_ids":[7]},{"right":"275px","width":"380px","text":"הוּא! אִי דִּרְמָא <span class=\"ein_mishpat_marker\" data-ein-mishpat-id=\"7\" data-marker-letter=\"ח\">ח</span>תְּלָתָא וַאֲתָא תְּלָתָא וּפַלְגָא,","segment_ids":[7]},{"right":"275px","width":"380px","text":"פְּלוּגְתָּא דְּרַבָּנַן וַאֲחֵרִים הִיא! <span class=\"sentence\" id=\"8\" type=\"start\">&star;</span>אֶלָּא לְמַעוֹטֵי","segment_ids":[8]},{"right":"275px","width":"380px","text":"<span class=\"ein_mishpat_marker\" data-ein-mishpat-id=\"8\" data-marker-letter=\"ט\">ט</span>שֶׁרֵיחוֹ רַע. וְאִיבָּעֵית אֵימָא: לְעוֹלָם לְמַעוֹטֵי מְגוּלֶּה –","segment_ids":[8]},{"right":"275px","width":"380px","text":"וְאַף עַל גַּב <span class=\"ein_mishpat_marker\" data-ein-mishpat-id=\"9\" data-marker-letter=\"י\">י</span>דְּעַבְּרֵיהּ בִּמְסַנֶּנֶת <span class=\"name-reference-marker name-reference-tanna\" data-authority-id=\"2266\" data-full-name=\"Rabbi Neḥemya I\" data-name-he=\"רבי נחמיה\" data-sage-type=\"tanna\" title=\"Rabbi Neḥemya I, fifth-generation Tanna\">כְּרַבִּי נְחֶמְיָה</span>,","segment_ids":[8]},{"right":"275px","width":"380px","text":"אֲפִילּוּ הָכִי – ״הַקְרִיבֵהוּ נָא לְפֶחָתֶךָ הֲיִרְצְךָ","segment_ids":[8]},{"right":"275px","width":"380px","text":"אוֹ הֲיִשָּׂא פָנֶיךָ״. <span class=\"sentence\" id=\"9\" type=\"start\">&star;</span>בְּעָא מִינֵּיהּ <span class=\"name-reference-marker name-reference-amora\" data-sage-type=\"amora\" title=\"Rav Kahana Chamuh Derav Mesharesheya, fourth-generation Amora\" data-authority-id=\"2019\" data-full-name=\"Rav Kahana Chamuh Derav Mesharesheya\" data-name-he=\"רב כהנא חמוה דרב משרשיא\" data-crossline-group=\"name-ref-crossline-5909\">רַב כָּהֲנָא חֲמוּהּ</span>","segment_ids":[9]},{"right":"275px","width":"380px","text":"<span class=\"name-reference-marker name-reference-amora\" data-sage-type=\"amora\" title=\"Rav Kahana Chamuh Derav Mesharesheya, fourth-generation Amora\" data-authority-id=\"2019\" data-full-name=\"Rav Kahana Chamuh Derav Mesharesheya\" data-name-he=\"רב כהנא חמוה דרב משרשיא\" data-crossline-group=\"name-ref-crossline-5909\">דְּרַב מְשַׁרְשְׁיָא</span> <span class=\"name-reference-marker name-reference-amora\" data-sage-type=\"amora\" title=\"Rava, fourth-generation Amora\" data-authority-id=\"2582\" data-full-name=\"Rava\" data-name-he=\"רָבָא\">מֵרָבָא</span>: חֲמַר חִוַּורְיָין, מַהוּ? אֲמַר","segment_ids":[9]},{"right":"275px","width":"380px","text":"<span class=\"ein_mishpat_marker\" data-ein-mishpat-id=\"10\" data-marker-letter=\"כ\">כ</span>לֵיהּ: ״אַל תֵּרֶא יַיִן כִּי יִתְאַדָּם״<span class=\"sugya-marker sugya-marker-vilna-piska\" data-raw-symbol=\"׃\" data-sugya-id=\"349\" data-sugya-kind=\"vilna-piska\">׃</span> <span class=\"sugya-marker sugya-marker-steinsaltz\" data-sentence-id=\"10\" data-sugya-id=\"344\" data-sugya-kind=\"steinsaltz\">§</span> <span class=\"sentence\" id=\"10\" type=\"start\">☆</span>קַנְקַנִּים בַּשָּׁרוֹן","segment_ids":[10]},{"right":"275px","width":"380px","text":"וְכוּ׳<span class=\"sugya-marker sugya-marker-vilna-piska\" data-raw-symbol=\"׃\" data-sugya-id=\"350\" data-sugya-kind=\"vilna-piska\">׃</span> <span class=\"ein_mishpat_marker\" data-ein-mishpat-id=\"11\" data-marker-letter=\"ל\">ל</span>תָּאנָא: פִּיטָסוֹת נָאוֹת וּמְגוּפָּרוֹת<span class=\"sugya-marker sugya-marker-vilna-piska\" data-raw-symbol=\"׃\" data-sugya-id=\"351\" data-sugya-kind=\"vilna-piska\">׃</span>","segment_ids":[10]},{"right":"275px","width":"380px","text":"<span class=\"sugya-marker sugya-marker-steinsaltz\" data-sentence-id=\"11\" data-steinsaltz-label=\"א\" data-sugya-id=\"345\" data-sugya-kind=\"steinsaltz\"></span> <span class=\"sentence\" id=\"11\" type=\"start\">☆</span><big><strong>מַתְנִי׳</strong></big> <span class=\"ein_mishpat_marker\" data-ein-mishpat-id=\"12\" data-marker-letter=\"מ\">מ</span>הַמּוֹכֵר יַיִן <span class=\"ein_mishpat_marker\" data-ein-mishpat-id=\"13\" data-marker-letter=\"נ\">נ</span>לַחֲבֵירוֹ, וְהֶחְמִיץ – אֵינוֹ","segment_ids":[11]},{"right":"275px","width":"380px","text":"חַיָּיב בְּאַחְרָיוּתוֹ. וְאִם יָדוּעַ שֶׁיֵּינוֹ מַחְמִיץ –","segment_ids":[11]},{"right":"275px","width":"380px","text":"הֲרֵי זֶה מִקָּח טָעוּת. וְאִם אָמַר לוֹ: ״יַיִן","segment_ids":[11]}],"rashi":[{"width":"450px","right":"","left":"0px","text":""},{"width":"450px","right":"","left":"0px","text":""},{"width":"450px","right":"","left":"0px","text":""},{"width":"450px","right":"","left":"0px","text":""},{"width":"250px","rig